EXPERIMENT: D11_MDM2_STRUCTURAL_REPURPOSING_v1
DATE: 2026-06-07
STATUS: pre-registered
DATASET: PRISM Repurposing 20Q2 Secondary Screen
DERIVES_FROM: D10_STRUCTURAL_CANCER_ONTOLOGY_v1 (analytical, no pre-reg required)

MOTIVATION:
D10 computed pairwise structural cosine similarity across 6 cancer networks.
Most structurally similar pair: PDAC ↔ BRAF-melanoma (cosine = +0.516),
despite completely different drivers (KRAS vs BRAF), tissue (pancreas vs skin),
and regime (ODS vs CLASS6b).

Shared structural signature: CDK4, TP53, MDM2, and AKT1 all in DAMPER class
in BOTH PDAC and BRAF-MEL. This is the p53-pathway structural convergence.

From D7 z_dr atlas (pre-registered before this):
  MDM2 in PDAC:     z1=+1.010, z2=+1.085 — robust DAMPER (structural target)
  CDK4 in PDAC:     z1=+2.513, z2=+2.277 — SIGNIFICANT DAMPER (strongest in atlas)
  TP53 in PDAC:     z1=+2.297, z2=+1.525 — robust DAMPER

From D10 raw delta_r:
  MDM2 PDAC:    +0.265 (highest MDM2 delta_r in atlas)
  MDM2 BRAF-MEL: +0.134 (second highest)
  MDM2 CRC:     −0.069 (ANCHOR — structural prediction: MDM2 inhibition ineffective)
  MDM2 KRAS-NSCLC: +0.100 (damper but weaker than PDAC)

STRUCTURAL PREDICTION:
MDM2 is a structural DAMPER in PDAC and BRAF-MEL, and an ANCHOR in CRC.
Per the boundary condition (D9): structural position predicts lethality when
target is directly co-pathway with the dependency-driver.

  PDAC: MDM2 is co-pathway with TP53, which is co-mutated with KRAS in PDAC
    (~70% TP53 mutation rate in PDAC). MDM2 regulates TP53 directly.
    HOWEVER: nutlin-class MDM2 inhibitors REQUIRE WILD-TYPE TP53 to kill cells.
    MDM2 inhibition reactivates p53 signaling; if TP53 is mutant, no signal.

  CRITICAL CONFOUND:
  PDAC has ~70% TP53 mutation rate in tumors. PRISM PDAC cell lines likely
  have a high TP53 mutation rate too. This means:
    - Structural prediction (MDM2 damper → kills PDAC): may be DENIED not because
      the framework is wrong, but because the drug mechanism requires TP53 WT.
    - If H1 is denied due to TP53 mutation prevalence, this is a GENOTYPE
      OVERRIDE of the structural prediction — same category as BRAF inhibitors
      in EGFR-NSCLC (D5 boundary condition).
    - If H1 is confirmed despite high TP53 mutation rate → structural position
      predicts even beyond genotype-level expectations.

  BRAF-MEL: MDM2 damper (+0.134). BRAF-melanoma has lower TP53 mutation rate
    (~14-17% in TCGA). CDK4/MDM2 co-amplification is a known secondary event
    alongside BRAF-V600E. Nutlin sensitivity in BRAF-MEL is less confounded by
    TP53 mutations.

  CRC: MDM2 ANCHOR (−0.069). Structural prediction: MDM2 inhibitors ineffective
    in CRC. Note: CRC also has ~60% TP53 mutation rate. Both structural AND
    genotype factors predict poor response.

DECISION TABLE FOR INTERPRETING OUTCOMES:
  H1 confirmed (PDAC kills more than CRC):
    → Structural prediction holds; TP53-WT PDAC lines dominate the signal
    → MDM2 is both a structural target AND pharmacologically relevant in PDAC
  H1 denied:
    → Two interpretations: (A) TP53 mutation prevalence overrides structural
      signal (genotype override of structural prediction — new boundary condition case);
      OR (B) structural position of MDM2 does not predict lethality even with
      direct co-pathway (TP53 MDM2 co-pathway exists in PDAC)
    → Cannot distinguish (A) vs (B) without TP53 stratification
  H2 confirmed (BRAF-MEL kills more than EGFR-NSCLC):
    → Cleaner structural test (lower TP53 mutation rate in BRAF-MEL)
    → Confirms cross-regime structural repurposing via shared structural motif
  H2 denied:
    → MDM2 structural position does not predict cross-cancer lethality
      even when structural signal is present

PRIMARY HYPOTHESIS (H1, CONFIRMATORY):
MDM2 inhibitors show significantly more negative mean LFC in PDAC cell lines
(primary_tissue='pancreas', n~36) than in CRC cell lines
(primary_tissue='colorectal', n=38).

MDM2 structural basis: robust DAMPER in PDAC (z1=+1.010, z2=+1.085);
ANCHOR in CRC (delta_r=−0.069). Direct MDM2→TP53 pathway exists in PDAC.
Statistical test: Mann-Whitney U (PDAC < CRC), p < 0.05

SECONDARY HYPOTHESIS (H2, CONFIRMATORY):
MDM2 inhibitors show significantly more negative mean LFC in BRAF-melanoma
(secondary_tissue='melanoma', n=44) than in EGFR-NSCLC
(primary_tissue='lung', secondary_tissue='lung_NSC', EGFR filter, n subset).

MDM2 structural basis: damper in BRAF-MEL (delta_r=+0.134);
near-neutral in EGFR-NSCLC (not in robust atlas).
TP53 confound: BRAF-MEL has lower TP53 mutation rate (~15%) vs EGFR-NSCLC (~50%).
Combined structural + genotype prediction: BRAF-MEL kills more.
Statistical test: Mann-Whitney U (MEL < EGFR-NSCLC), p < 0.05

EXPLORATORY (H3):
MDM2 inhibitors more negative in PDAC than KRAS-NSCLC.
PDAC MDM2 delta_r=+0.265 > KRAS-NSCLC delta_r=+0.100 (both dampers, PDAC stronger).
If confirmed: within-damper magnitude predicts relative lethality.

EXPLORATORY (H4):
Structural double dissociation: MDM2 inhibitors prefer PDAC/BRAF-MEL over CRC;
CDK4/6 inhibitors (D8 H3: no PDAC preference) are used as negative structural control.
If MDM2 shows PDAC preference where CDK4/6 did not (D8 H3 not supported),
it distinguishes MDM2-specific structural prediction from CDK4-specific failure.

MDM2 DRUGS IN PRISM (confirmed before LFC access from treatment info only):
Primary: nutlin-3a (MDM2 inhibitor, ~24-48 entries in PRISM)
Extended: RG7112 (first clinical MDM2i), AMG-232, idasanutlin (RG7388),
          MI-773 (SAR405838), HDM201

CELL LINES:
  PDAC: primary_tissue='pancreas' (n~36 from PRISM)
  CRC: primary_tissue='colorectal' (n=38)
  BRAF-MEL: secondary_tissue='melanoma' (n=44)
  EGFR-NSCLC: primary_tissue='lung', secondary_tissue='lung_NSC' (subset)
  KRAS-NSCLC: same lung NSC lines (comparison control, H3)

STRUCTURAL CHAIN OF EVIDENCE (pre-registered lineage):
  D7 (9dc1b1d) → MDM2 in PDAC: robust DAMPER (z1=+1.010, z2=+1.085)
  D10 (no pre-reg, analytical) → PDAC-BRAF-MEL structural partnership
  D11 (this pre-reg) → MDM2 pharmacogenomics: structural prediction to lethality

BOUNDARY CONDITION CONTEXT:
This test falls in the "direct co-pathway" category (strict boundary from D9):
  MDM2 → TP53 is a direct interaction (MDM2 is the primary TP53 ubiquitin ligase)
  TP53 is co-mutated with KRAS in PDAC (KRAS activates → KRAS-driven proliferation
  requires bypassing TP53-mediated apoptosis → TP53 loss or MDM2 amplification)
  MDM2 is co-pathway with the PDAC network's key structural axis.

However: the GENOTYPE confound (TP53 mutation required for nutlin to work) means
this is a boundary condition TEST of genotype-override vs structural-override.
The outcome clarifies whether structural position or genotypic context dominates.

FALSIFICATION CRITERIA:
H1 DENIED + H2 DENIED → MDM2 structural prediction fails; p53-pathway structural
  dampers do not predict pharmacological lethality (framework scope: more limited)
H1 DENIED + H2 CONFIRMED → Genotype override in PDAC (TP53-mutant prevalence);
  structural prediction works where genotype aligns (BRAF-MEL)
H1 CONFIRMED + H2 CONFIRMED → Structural cross-regime repurposing prediction
  confirmed; MDM2 inhibitors as PDAC+BRAF-MEL dual-cancer candidates
